<p>
  <b><font size=+3>Information Theory Lecture: Material and Organisation</font></b>
  </p>
<br>
The class is taught by 	Michèle Wigger (michele.wigger@telecom-paris.fr), office number 3C52.<br>
<br>
TD sessions are  taught by Basile Buffin (basile.buffin@ip-paris.fr).<br>



There will be a final exam, contributing 90% of the grade. 10% of the grade can be obtained by handing in solutions to exercises.
<br>

The main reference for this class is the book "Elements of Information Theory" by Cover and Thomas, 2nd edition. The section and chapter numbers below in the programme refer to this book. 

<p>
<b><font size=+2>Programme</font></b>
</p>

<li> Class on 17/9/2025: Entropy, Divergence, Mutual Information and Properties (Sections 2.1-2.5) </li>
<li> Class on 24/9/2025: Source Codes, Kraft's Inequality, Bounds on Minimum Description Lengths (Sections 5.1-5.6)</li>
<li> Class on 1/10/2025: Entropy Rates, Markov Chains (Sections 4.1 and 4.2)</li>
<li> Class on 8/10/2025: Arithmetic Coding and Universal Source Coding (Section 5.10 and 12.3)</li>
<li> Class on 8/10/2025: Method of Types</li>
<li> Class on 15/10/2025: Channel Capacity (Sections 8.1-8.4)</li>
<li> Class on 22/10/2025: Proof of Channel Capacity (Sections 8.1-8.4, 8.7, 8.12) and  Joint Source Channel Coding</li>
<li> Class on 5/111/2025:  Rate-Distortion Theory (Sections 8.13 and 13.1-13.3)</li>
<li> Class on 5/111/2025: Advanced Compression (Slepian-Wolf and Wyner-Ziv) (Sections 8.13 and 13.1-13.3)</li>


